3. Close Behavior Stabilized

Close now:

Clears Dish state
Clears local component state
Navigates to Dish List

Added:

storeValue("current_dish_id", 0)
removeValue("dsh_components_local_rows")

before navigation.

4. Table Reset Was Damaging Component Table

Important discovery:

Using:

resetWidget("tblDshComponents")

was corrupting table configuration.

Observed symptoms:

Frozen cells
Supabase column names appearing
Table column configuration breaking

Fix:

Commented out all:

await this.safeReset("tblDshComponents");

occurrences.

Result:

Component table no longer corrupts during Close / Save & New.

5. dshCompTable Lifecycle Bug Found

A real bug was identified:

Rows created during New Dish carried:

dish_id = 0

After save:

current_dish_id = new ID

but rows still referenced:

dish_id = 0

which caused:

getRows()

to discard them.

Result:

Page appeared to clear after save.

A revised getRows() was implemented to allow draft rows to be adopted by the newly created Dish.

This was a genuine lifecycle bug.

